definitions.definition: A place where items may be accumulated or routinely kept .
examples: This building used to be a store for old tires.

definitions.definition: A place where items may be purchased ; a shop .
examples: I need to get some milk from the grocery store .
The main store of 1000 36-bit words seemed large at the time.

definitions.definition: A great quantity or number; abundance .
A head of store cattle ( feeder cattle to be sold to others for finishing); a store cattle beast.

main_definition: A place where items may be accumulated or routinely kept .
secondary_definitions: ( mainly North American ) A place where items may be purchased ; a shop .
A great quantity or number; abundance .
A head of store cattle ( feeder cattle to be sold to others for finishing); a store cattle beast.
